> We love black beans for the drama that their jet-bead good looks can bring to a dish. But for less shallow reasons too! Simultaneously nutty and creamy, they're a good source of both protein and fibre and make a delicious addition to this zingy, Mexican-inspired dish of butternut squash, quinoa and avocado. Enjoy!

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve the @butternut squash{1} lengthways and scoop out the seeds (no need to peel). Chop it into 2cm cubes and place on a lightly oiled #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over half the @Mexican style spice mix{1} and a pinch of @salt{}. Toss to coat then spread out evenly and roast on the top shelf of your oven until charred at the edges, ~{30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Put a large #saucepan{} of @water{500} on to boil. When boiling, add the @vegetable stock powder{1/2} and stir to dissolve. Lower the heat to medium and add the @quinoa{120}. Cook uncovered, until the quinoa is tender and the seed has split, ~{11-12%minutes}. When done, drain in a #sieve{} and leave to cool.

Chop the @medium tomato{2} into 1cm chunks. Pop in a #mixing bowl{} and season with a pinch of @salt{}. Halve the @avocado{1} lengthways and twist apart. Remove the stone and scoop out the flesh with a #spoon{}. Chop the flesh into 1cm chunks and add to the tomato. Zest the @lime{1}. Mix half the zest into the salsa, along with a squeeze of lime juice. Mix well and set aside.

Drain the @black beans{1} in a #colander{} and rinse under cold water. Add to the salsa. Pick the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). Add half to the salsa. Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all) and stir it in too. Add a pinch of the remaining fajita seasoning and the @olive oil{1}. Taste and adjust with @?salt{}, @?black pepper{} or more spice if you like it hot!

Mix the remaining chopped mint through the @soured cream{150}. Add a pinch of @salt{} and set aside. Transfer the (now cooled) quinoa to a large #bowl{} and add a squeeze of lime juice, the remaining zest and a pinch of fajita seasoning. Mix together and add salt to taste.

Stir half the salsa through the quinoa, then spoon the quinoa into deep #bowls{}. Top with the butternut squash and the remaining salsa. Dollop on some sour cream and sprinkle over the @pumpkin seeds{15}. Enjoy!